226static void endCall(JNIEnv* env)
227{
228 jobject exh = (*env)->ExceptionOccurred(env);
229 if(exh != 0)
230 (*env)->ExceptionClear(env);
231
232 if(s_doMonitorOps && ((*env)->MonitorEnter(env, s_threadLock) < 0))
233 elog(ERROR, "Java enter monitor failure");
234
235 jniEnv = env;
236 if(exh != 0)
237 {
238 printStacktrace(env, exh);
239 if((*env)->IsInstanceOf(env, exh, ServerException_class))
240 {
241 /* Rethrow the server error.
242 */
243 jobject jed = (*env)->CallObjectMethod(env, exh, ServerException_getErrorData);
244 if ( 0 != (*env)->ExceptionOccurred(env) )
245 {
246 (*env)->ExceptionClear(env);
247 jed = 0;
248 }
249
250 if(jed != 0)
251 ReThrowError(pljava_ErrorData_getErrorData(jed));
252 }
253 /* There's no return from this call.
254 */
255 elogExceptionMessage(env, exh, ERROR);
256 }

289bool beginNativeNoErrCheck(JNIEnv* env)
290{
291 if ( s_refuseOtherThreads && env != primordialJNIEnv )
292 {
293 env = JNI_setEnv(env);
294 Exception_throw(ERRCODE_INTERNAL_ERROR,
295 "Attempt by non-initial thread to enter PostgreSQL from Java");
296 JNI_setEnv(env);
297 return false;
298 }
299
300 if((env = JNI_setEnv(env)) != 0)
301 {
302 /* The backend is *not* awaiting the return of a call to the JVM
303 * so there's no way the JVM can be allowed to call out at this
304 * point.
305 */
306 Exception_throw(ERRCODE_INTERNAL_ERROR,
307 "An attempt was made to call a PostgreSQL backend function while main thread was not in the JVM");
308 JNI_setEnv(env);
309 return false;
310 }
311 return true;
312}
313
314bool beginNative(JNIEnv* env)
315{
316 if (!currentInvocation)
317 {
318 env = JNI_setEnv(env);
319 Exception_throw(ERRCODE_INTERNAL_ERROR, "An attempt was made to call a PostgreSQL backend function in a transaction callback. At the end of a transaction you may not access the database any longer.");
320 JNI_setEnv(env);
321 return false;
322 }
323
324 if(currentInvocation->errorOccurred)
325 {
326 /* An elog with level higher than ERROR was issued. The transaction
327 * state is unknown. There's no way the JVM is allowed to enter the
328 * backend at this point.
329 */
330 env = JNI_setEnv(env);
331 Exception_throw(ERRCODE_INTERNAL_ERROR,
332 "An attempt was made to call a PostgreSQL backend function after an elog(ERROR) had been issued");
333 JNI_setEnv(env);
334 return false;
335 }
336 return beginNativeNoErrCheck(env);
337}

877jint JNI_createVM(JavaVM** javaVM, JavaVMInitArgs* vmArgs)
878{
879 JNIEnv* env = 0;
880 jint jstat = pljava_createvm(javaVM, (void **)&env, vmArgs);
881 if(jstat == JNI_OK)
882 {
883 jniEnv = env;
884 primordialJNIEnv = env;
885 mainThreadId = env;
886 }
887 return jstat;
888}

937
938void JNI_exceptionDescribe(void)
939{
940 /* The ExceptionDescribe will print on stderr. Not a good idea
941 * since the exception itself might have been caused by an unwriteable
942 * stdout/stderr (happens when running as a windows service
943 *
944 * (*env)->ExceptionDescribe(env);
945 */
946 jthrowable exh;
947 BEGIN_JAVA
948 exh = (*env)->ExceptionOccurred(env);
949 if(exh != 0)
950 {
951 (*env)->ExceptionClear(env);
952 printStacktrace(env, exh);
953 elogExceptionMessage(env, exh, WARNING);
954 }
955 END_JAVA
956}

959{
960 jthrowable result;

963 END_JAVA
964 return result;
965}

1041
1042jfieldID JNI_getFieldIDOrNull(jclass clazz, const char* name, const char* sig)
1043{
1044 jfieldID result;
1045 jobject exh;
1046 BEGIN_CALL
1047 result = (*env)->GetFieldID(env, clazz, name, sig);
1048 if(result == 0) {
1049 exh = (*env)->ExceptionOccurred(env);
1050 if ( 0 != exh )
1051 {
1052 /*
1053 * Ignore a NoSuchFieldError, but not any other exception.
1054 * This operation order (first clear the pending exception, then
1055 * do the IsInstanceOf check, then Throw again if not the expected
1056 * class) avoids a benign -Xcheck:JNI warning about calling
1057 * IsInstanceOf while an exception is pending.
1058 */
1059 (*env)->ExceptionClear(env);
1060 if ( ! (*env)->IsInstanceOf(env, exh, NoSuchFieldError_class) )
1061 (*env)->Throw(env, exh);
1062 (*env)->DeleteLocalRef(env, exh);
1063 }
1064 }
1065 END_CALL
1066 return result;
1067}

1259jboolean JNI_hasNullArrayElement(jobjectArray array)
1260{
1261 jsize idx;
1262 jboolean foundNull = JNI_FALSE;
1263 BEGIN_JAVA
1264 idx = (*env)->GetArrayLength(env, array);
1265 while(--idx >= 0)
1266 {
1267 if((*env)->GetObjectArrayElement(env, array, idx) != 0)
1268 continue;
1269 foundNull = JNI_TRUE;
1270 break;
1271 }
1272 END_JAVA
1273 return foundNull;

1632/*
1633 * Implementations of the context class loader updater and restorer.
1634 * The loader reference passed in is not to be deleted. If saved anywhere,
1635 * a new global ref is to be taken, and later deleted when restored.
1636 */
1637
1638static inline void _updaterCommon(JNIEnv *env, jobject thread, jobject loader)
1639{
1640 jobject old = (*env)->GetObjectField(env, thread, s_Thread_contextLoader);
1641
1642 /*
1643 * If it is not already the loader we want, change it, and set
1644 * currentInvocation->savedLoader to restore it later. If this is
1645 * a top-level invocation, we don't care what it gets restored to, so lie,
1646 * and save loader there instead of old. If there are many consecutive
1647 * top-level calls with the same context loader, that will save work later.
1648 *
1649 * If it is already the loader we want, again we check for a top-level call,
1650 * and can leave currentInvocation->savedLoader completely unset in that
1651 * case, so the restore call will be skipped completely. If not a top-level
1652 * call, though, see that it gets restored to what the caller might expect,
1653 * even if it somehow got changed.
1654 */
1655
1656 if ( ! (*env)->IsSameObject(env, old, loader) )
1657 {
1658 (*env)->SetObjectField(env, thread, s_Thread_contextLoader, loader);
1659
1660 currentInvocation->savedLoader = (*env)->NewGlobalRef(env,
1661 ( NULL == currentInvocation->previous ) ? loader : old);
1662 }
1663 else if ( NULL != currentInvocation->previous )
1664 currentInvocation->savedLoader = (*env)->NewGlobalRef(env, old);
1665
1666 (*env)->DeleteLocalRef(env, old);
1667}
1668
1669static void _heavyUpdater(jobject loader)
1670{
1671 jobject thread;
1672 jobject exh;
1673
1674 BEGIN_JAVA
1675
1676 thread =
1677 (*env)->CallStaticObjectMethod(env,
1678 s_Thread_class, s_Thread_currentThread); /* should never fail */
1679
1680 exh = (*env)->ExceptionOccurred(env); /* but mollify -Xcheck:jni anyway */
1681 if(exh != 0)
1682 {
1683 (*env)->ExceptionClear(env);
1684 elogExceptionMessage(env, exh, ERROR);
1685 }
1686
1687 _updaterCommon(env, thread, loader);
1688
1689 (*env)->DeleteLocalRef(env, thread);
1690
1691 END_JAVA
1692}
1693
1694void _heavyRestorer()
1695{
1696 jobject thread;
1697 jobject value;
1698 jobject exh;
1699
1700 BEGIN_JAVA
1701
1702 thread =
1703 (*env)->CallStaticObjectMethod(env,
1704 s_Thread_class, s_Thread_currentThread); /* should never fail */
1705
1706 exh = (*env)->ExceptionOccurred(env); /* but mollify -Xcheck:jni anyway */
1707 if(exh != 0)
1708 {
1709 (*env)->ExceptionClear(env);
1710 elogExceptionMessage(env, exh, ERROR);
1711 }
1712
1713 value = currentInvocation->savedLoader;
1714
1715 (*env)->SetObjectField(env, thread, s_Thread_contextLoader, value);
1716 (*env)->DeleteGlobalRef(env, value);
1717 (*env)->DeleteLocalRef(env, thread);
1718
1719 END_JAVA
1720}
